 and 1,950 liters of Diesel. The seizure also include 3,250 liters of Kerosene, 73 packets of handbags (New) 33 cartons body cream, 2 sacks of margarine (Blue band) 149 bags by 50kg and 3 cartons of Sugar, 26 sacks of Kolanut, 7 sacks of Bitter kola, 55 sacks of Cannabis sativa, 5 bundles and 9 pack of used tyres, 2 cartons of Milk 12 cartons of Spaghetti, 40 drums of Ethanol (alcoholic spirit), 9 cartons of mosquito coil and flit, 90 packs of pineapple, 17 cartons of fresh herbal soap and 697 bags of Sodium Hydroxide Chemical He added that the total duty paid value of the items is N500,766,215 The Area Controller said as you all know that the border is still closed to import/export and this made our traditional revenue not feasible. We are able to generate some fees as stated below, from the sales of Petroleum products and other perishables that cannot be warehoused. Agbara pointed out that the Command was able to achieve the feat due to strategic enforcement measures put in place, despite the increasing state of Covid-19 pandemic ravaging the country. He assured that “the Command will continue to dialogue, engage, sensitize and educate the public on social/economic implication of smuggling as well as performing the statutory function of enforcing compliance in line with government fiscal policies”. “We wish to reiterate that the continued attack on operatives of NCS and other sister agencies will not deter us from the continued performance of our legitimate duties”. Agbara appealed to parents and guardians to prevail on their children, wards, and youths to desist from such criminal acts as the NCS operatives in observance of the rules of engagement will be left with no choice than to defend their lives if attacked. “The anti-smuggling embarked upon by the Command is a patriotic duty in the interest of national security and economic wellbeing of Nigeria”. Vanguard Apparently, the Ogun Area Command of Nigeria Customs Service, NCS, is in a rage against unrepentant smugglers operating within its area of coverage. June 13, 2019 In "News" Despite all the challenging operating environment, the Ogun State Command, Nigeria Customs Service, NCS, recorded major offensive against smugglers plying the area with the seizure of a total of  6, 015 units of 50 kg of contraband rice and 67 vehicles last month, November, 2018. December 12, 2018 In "Maritime Report" The Ogun State Area Command of Nigeria Customs Service, NCS, has recorded huge revenue generation of N2.6billion from January to June 2018, economic year. July 9, 2018 In "News"